    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid, with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>free</strong> <strong>range</strong> <strong>chicken thighs</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min until the chicken is lightly golden and the onion<strong> </strong>is<strong> </strong>starting to soften</p>",
